verbose_text: In addition to its widely reported activation of Nrf2 in CNS cells, in vitro DMF treatment of peripheral immune cells has been shown to affect NF-kappaB activation and production of a variety of inflammatory mediators; we have previously demonstrated that DMF stimulates production of the immunomodulator cAMP via the prostaglandin E2 receptor in PBMCs, but only at relatively high concentrations of DMF [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR].
evidence: DMF stimulates production of the immunomodulator cAMP
